message: teens and young adults can potentially become victims by doing seemingly normal things like dating, playing sports, going to school or visiting local youth hangouts.  “It could be they are dropped off at school, and once the parent drives away, they could be picked up by a trafficker and then returned… It could be staying after school, but not really staying after school,”

data.description: Teens and young adults can find themselves susceptible to more than just growing pains — those ages 12 to 25 are among the most susceptible to human traffickers.
data.title: Kiwanis to host presentation on human trafficking in New Baltimore
